pages/_document.js
pages/_app.js
pages/api/
For example, if you reconfigure .ts page extensions to .page.ts, you would need to rename pages like middleware.page.ts, instrumentation.page.ts, _app.page.ts.Including non-page files in the pages directory




You can colocate test files or other files used by components in the pages directory. Inside next.config.js, add the pageExtensions config:next.config.jsmodule.exports = {
  pageExtensions: ['page.tsx', 'page.ts', 'page.jsx', 'page.js'],
